attribute.title: actual_bitdepth
attribute.description: This value shall contain a positive integer that gives the actual bit-depth for each pixel. This is corresponding to a dynamic range of the raw (l2a) image for ONC. Although the l2a data is stored in a 16-bit integer image array, the bit depth used for nominal image acquisition is 12. A bit depth is reduced to 10 or 8 bit for some images during digital processing in DE or ONC-E dividing the original data by 2 or 4.

PermissibleValue.valueMeaning: 10-bit
12-bit
8-bit

attribute.title: band_center
attribute.description: This value shall contain an real number that gives an effective band center of a selected band or camera in micrometers. For ONC, this value is calculated using the system efficiency of a specific camera or band, and this value is used to calculate the sensitivity and effective solar irradiance utilized in creation of l2c and l2d.
attribute.unitId: AU, Angstrom, cm, km, m, micrometer, mm, nm

attribute.title: bandwidth
attribute.description: This value shall contain an real number that gives an effective band with of a selected band or camera in micrometers. For ONC, this value is calculated using the system efficiency of a specific camera or band, and this value is used to calculate the sensitivity and effective solar irradiance utilized in creation of l2c and l2d.
attribute.unitId: AU, Angstrom, cm, km, m, micrometer, mm, nm

attribute.title: declination_at_center
attribute.description: The value field shall contain a real number that gives declination of the center of the image in degrees, in J2000 frame.
attribute.unitId: arcmin, arcsec, deg, hr, mrad, rad

attribute.title: declination_at_lower_left_corner
attribute.description: The value field shall contain a real number that gives declination of the lower-left corner of the image in degrees, in J2000 frame.
attribute.unitId: arcmin, arcsec, deg, hr, mrad, rad

attribute.title: declination_at_lower_right_corner
attribute.description: The value field shall contain a real number that gives declination of the lower-right corner of the image in degrees, in J2000 frame.
attribute.unitId: arcmin, arcsec, deg, hr, mrad, rad

attribute.title: declination_at_upper_left_corner
attribute.description: The value field shall contain a real number that gives declination of the upper-left corner of the image in degrees, in J2000 frame.
attribute.unitId: arcmin, arcsec, deg, hr, mrad, rad

attribute.title: declination_at_upper_right_corner

attribute.unitId: arcmin, arcsec, deg, hr, mrad, rad

attribute.title: exposure_duration
attribute.description: The value field shall contain a real number giving the exposure time of the observation in units of seconds. When the number of sub images is 2 for ONC image, this value is for main image. When the number of sub images is more than 2 for ONC image, this value indicates an exposure time for each image.
attribute.unitId: day, hr, julian day, microseconds, min, ms, s, yr

attribute.title: filter_name
attribute.description: The value field shall contain a character string that gives the name of the filter that was used during the observation to select or modify the radiation that was transmitted to the detector. The value 'None' indicates that no filter was used.

PermissibleValue.valueMeaning: This value means the filter for the wavelengths ranged from 8 micrometer to 12 micrometer is used.
This value means the ul-band filter is used.
This value means the wide-band is used.
This value means the v-band is used.
This value means the w-band is used.
This value means the x-band is used.
This value means the Na-band is used.
This value means the p-band is used.
This value means the b-band is used.
No filter is used.

attribute.title: horizontal_instantaneous_field_of_view
attribute.description: The value field shall contain a real number that gives the horizontal instantaneous field of view.
attribute.unitId: arcmin, arcsec, deg, hr, mrad, rad

attribute.title: image_compression_algorithm
attribute.description: The value field shall contain a character string identifying the algorithm of image compression.

PermissibleValue.valueMeaning: No compression algorithm is used.
StarPixel Flexible compression algorithm is used.
StarPixel Lossless compression algorithm is used.

attribute.title: image_compression_initial_subsampling_interval
attribute.description: The value field shall contain a non-negative integer that gives value of exponent n for initial subsampling interval that is 2**n (see Takada+2007).

attribute.title: image_compression_quality
attribute.description: The value field shall contain a non-negative real number that gives the value of quality degradation parameter. The value of quality degradation parameter is set by command from the ground in 8 bits, but only upper 4 bits are included in the telemetry. The value of quality parameter should be within the range from 0 to 31.875 (= 0.125*2**8) if value of observation_mode is Science, and from 0 to 15.875 (= 0.125*2**7) if value of observation_mode is Navigation Dump. The value of quality degradation parameter is higher, quality of lossy compressed image will be worse, and the value is lower, the quality will be fine. If value of quality degradation parameter is 0, there will be no quality degradation.

attribute.title: image_compression_type
attribute.description: The value field shall contain a character string identifying the type of image compression on the onboard computer of the spacecraft.

PermissibleValue.valueMeaning: Lossless compression algorithm is used.
Lossy compression algorithm is used.
No compression algorithm is used.

attribute.title: image_processing_return_status
attribute.description: This value shall contain a character string that gives an image processing error log.

PermissibleValue.valueMeaning: This value means that error related to buffer size on image processing occurred, e.g., image sizes of two buffers specified as two operands of image processing command differ, buffer sizes of source and destination buffers differ.
This value means that error on hardware operation occurred, e.g., memory race condition, hardware operation does not finished until prescribed duration (timeout).
Image processing is completed normally.
This value means that image processing was interrupted for some reason.
This value means that overflow occurred during image processing.
This value means that both of overflow and underflow occurred during image processing.
This value means that invalid arguments have been passed to image processing command which is sent to DE or ONC-E.
This value means that underflow occurred during image processing.
This value means that zero division occurred during image processing.

attribute.title: number_of_binning
attribute.description: The value field shall contain a positive integer that gives the size of the area used for onboard binning. For example, if this value is 1, no binning was conducted. If this value is 2, the area of 2 x 2 pixels is binned to one pixel.

PermissibleValue.valueMeaning: No-binning
2x2 pixels binning
4x4 pixels binning
8x8 pixels binning

attribute.title: x_lower_left_corner
attribute.description: The value field shall contain a positive integer that gives the horizontal position of lower-left corner of the area selected as ROI (region of interest) in the full-size image coordinate system. Note that the origin is (1, 1) and the position in integer means center of the pixel. Possible values are 1, 129, 385, 513, 641, 769, and 897 for ONC image.

attribute.title: x_upper_right_corner
attribute.description: The value field shall contain a positive integer that gives the horizontal position of upper right corner of the area selected as ROI (region of interest) in the full-size image coordinate system. Note that the origin is (1, 1) and the position in integer means center of the pixel. Possible values are 129, 385, 513, 641, 769, 897, and 1024 for ONC frame image, and 32 for ONC optical black image.

attribute.title: y_lower_left_corner
attribute.description: The value field shall contain a positive integer that gives vertical-position of the lower-left corner of the area selected as ROI (region of interest) in the full-size image coordinate system. Note that the origin is (1, 1) and the position in integer means center of the pixel. Possible values are 1, 129, 385, 513, 641, 769, and 897 for ONC image.

attribute.title: y_upper_right_corner
attribute.description: The value field shall contain a positive integer that gives the vertical position of upper right corner of the area selected as ROI (region of interest) in the full-size image coordinate system. Note that the origin is (1, 1) and the position in integer means center of the pixel. Possbile values are 129, 385, 513, 641, 769, 897, 1024 for ONC image.

attribute.description: The value field shall contain a character string that describes the mission phase name.

PermissibleValue.valueMeaning: This is a name of mission phase that period is from 2018-06-03T05:59:00Z to 2018-06-27T00:35:00Z.
This is a name of mission phase that period is from 2018-06-27T00:35:00Z to 2019-11-13T01:00:00Z.
This is a name of mission phase that period is from 2014-12-03T04:22:04Z to 2015-03-03T00:00:00Z.

This is a name of mission phase that period is from 2015-03-03T00:00:00Z to 2015-10-01T00:00:00Z. EDVEGA is the acronym of Electric Delta-V Earth Gravity Assist which means accelerating spacecraft (delta-V) using electric propulsion and Earth swing-by.
This is a name of mission phase that period is from 2015-10-01T00:00:00Z to 2015-12-22T14:10:00Z.
This is a name of mission phase that period is from 2019-11-13T01:00:00Z.
This is a name of mission phase that period is from 2015-12-22T14:10:00Z to 2018-06-03T05:59:00Z.

attribute.title: normalization
attribute.description: This value shall contain a character string that gives whether data is normalized or not. This value shall contain a character string that gives a status of normalization. This normalization is conducted only for flat fields. All pixel values of the flat fields are divided by the average of the pixels in the central area (300 x 300 pixels).

PermissibleValue.valueMeaning: Data is normalized.
Data is not normalized.

PermissibleValue.valueMeaning: After Touch Down 2, i.e., after 2019-07-11T01:06:22.
Applicable to all periods
Period before touch down 1, i.e., from 2014-12-03T04:22:04 to 2019-02-21T22:29:13.

PermissibleValue.value: Between Touch Down 1 and Touch Down 2
PermissibleValue.valueMeaning: Between Touch Down 1 and Touch Down 2, i.e., from 2019-02-21T22:29:13 to 2019-07-11T01:06:22.

attribute.title: dynamic_range
attribute.description: The value field shall contain a real number that gives a full dynamic range of pixel value at the center of field-of-view, that is 4095 DU - bias, where bias is typically about 300 DU. A dynamic range of pixel value at other place on the detector is less than the value at the center of field-of-view due to vignetting effect. When lineaity correction is not conducted, values between linearity_guaranteed_range and this value are not trustworthy.

attribute.title: first_rotation_angle_for_stray_light
attribute.description: This value shall contain a real number that gives a rotation angle around the spacecraft +Y-axis from the reference spacecraft attitude which has the spacecraft +Z-axis is same as the Sun direction vector. This angle is utilized to define the magnitude of the radiator stray light of ONC-T. When second_rotation_angle_for_stray_light is larger than -7 degrees and first_rotation_angle_for_stray_light is smaller than -5 degrees, the radiator stray light of ONC-T exceeds 1 count per second.
attribute.unitId: arcmin, arcsec, deg, hr, mrad, rad

attribute.title: linearity_guaranteed_range
attribute.description: This value shall contain a positive real number that gives a maximum value of the linearity guaranteed range at the center of field-of-view. This value corresponds to about 3100 counts at the center of field-of-view. A maximum value of the linearity guaranteed range at other place on the detector is less than the value at the center of field-of-view due to vignetting effect. The values less than this value are trustworthy even if the nonlinearity correction is not conducted.

attribute.title: number_of_subimage
attribute.description: This value shall contain the number of sub images used to create image onboard. For ONC-T image, typical numbers are 1 for a raw image, 2 for a onboard smear reduction image, and more than 2 for onboard stacking image.

attribute.title: observation_mode
attribute.description: This value shall contain a character string that gives the name of the observation mode.

PermissibleValue.valueMeaning: This value indicates that the image is acquired for navigation purpose.
This value indicates that the image is acquired for science purpose. Such images are basically used to be applied science product procedure (Level 2a and later).

attribute.title: second_rotation_angle_for_stray_light
attribute.description: This value shall contain a real number that gives an rotation angle around the spacecraft +Z-axis from the spacecraft attitude after rotation around the spacecraft +Y-axis of first_rotation_angle_for_stray_light from the reference spacecraft attitude which has the spacecraft +Z-axis is same as the Sun direction vector. This angle is utilized to define the magnitude of the radiator stray light of ONC-T. When second_rotation_angle_for_stray_light is larger than -7 degrees and first_rotation_angle_for_stray_light is smaller than -5 degrees, the radiator stray light of ONC-T exceeds 1 count per second.
attribute.unitId: arcmin, arcsec, deg, hr, mrad, rad

attribute.title: stray_light_status
attribute.description: The value field shall contain a character string that gives whether stray light from the backward space of ONC-T exists or not. This value is only applied to ONC-T image. This value is estimated from the values of first_rotation_angle_for_stray_light, second_rotation_angle_for_stray_light, and empirical formula. See Suzuki+2018 and Tatsumi+2019 for the details.

PermissibleValue.valueMeaning: This image is estimated as affected by stray light from backside of the camera.
This image is estimated as not affected by stray light from backside of the camera.
The stray light could not be estimated because angle information are missing due to some reasons.

attribute.title: stray_light_correction_status

PermissibleValue.valueMeaning: Stray light correction is applied.
Stray light correction is not applied.

attribute.title: stray_light_second_principal_component_file_name

attribute.title: temperature_dependent_flat_field_correction_file_name

attribute.title: observation_date_time

attribute.description: The value field shall contain a character string that gives the stop of observation time in UTC.

attribute.title: raw_file_name
attribute.description: The value field shall contain a character string giving the file name of the raw data in level 0 that is the source of this file.

attribute.title: spacecraft_clock_start_count
attribute.description: The value field shall contain a character string that gives the spacecraft clock start count.

attribute.title: spacecraft_clock_stop_count
attribute.description: The value field shall contain a character string that gives the spacecraft clock stop count.

attribute.title: analog_electronics_mode
attribute.description: This value shall contain a string that gives a mode of ONC-AE, ONC analogue data processing unit.

PermissibleValue.valueMeaning: The mode is "shot".
The mode is "standby".

attribute.title: digital_electronics_selection
attribute.description: This value shall contain a string that gives which digital electronics, either of ONC-E or DE is selected for n-th sub image, where n is sequence_number. Basically, DE is selected for digital processing for scientific purpose, whereas ONC-E is selected for optical navigation.

PermissibleValue.valueMeaning: DE (Digital Electronics) is used for digital data processing.
ONC-E is used for digital data processing.

attribute.title: filter_wheel_driver_driving_status
attribute.description: This value shall contain a character string that gives the driving status of the ONC-T filter wheel driver for n-th sub image, where n is sequence_number.

PermissibleValue.valueMeaning: Filter wheel driver is driving.
Filter wheel driver is stopped.

attribute.title: filter_wheel_driver_null_position_flag
attribute.description: This value shall contain a character string that gives a filter wheel driver null position flag for n-th sub image, where n is sequence_number.

PermissibleValue.valueMeaning: Null point of the filter wheel is detected.
Null point of the filter wheel is not detected.

attribute.title: filter_wheel_driver_position_sensor_status
attribute.description: This value shall contain a character string that gives the status of "filter wheel position sensor" for n-th sub image, where n is sequence_number.

PermissibleValue.valueMeaning: Position sensor is off.
Position sensor is on.

attribute.title: filter_wheel_driver_reset_status
attribute.description: This value shall contain a character string to describe whether filter wheel driver is in reset sequence or not for n-th sub image, where n is sequence_number.

PermissibleValue.valueMeaning: Filter wheel driver is in reset sequence.
Filter wheel driver is not in reset sequence.

attribute.title: filter_wheel_driver_step_counter
attribute.description: This value shall contain an integer that gives the step counter of filter wheel driver for n-th sub image, where n is sequence_counter. This value increases every 1/4800 rotation, thus this value becomes 4800 after one filter wheel rotation.

attribute.title: filter_wheel_driver_step_counter_error_count
attribute.description: This value shall contain a non-negative integer that gives a error counter of filter wheel driver step counter.

attribute.title: filter_wheel_driver_timeout_error_count
attribute.description: This value shall contain an integer number that gives a filter wheel driver timeout error count in 4 bits for n-th sub image, where n is sequence_number.

attribute.title: flash_lamp_status
attribute.description: This value shall contain a string that gives the status of the flash lamp for n-th sub image, where n is sequence_number. The flash lamp is attached to illuminate target marker for ONC-W1 image. This value is usually set to be "Disable", and is switched to "Enable" for target marker tracking.

PermissibleValue.valueMeaning: Imaging when the flash lamp is off.
Imaging when the flash lamp is on.

attribute.title: flat_field_lamp_a_status
attribute.description: This value shall contain a character string that gives a status of flat field (FF) lamp A for n-th sub image, where n is sequence_number. FF lamps are attached in front of ONC-T lens system for calibration.

PermissibleValue.valueMeaning: The lamp A is on, and the voltage mode is high.
The lamp A is on, and the voltage mode is low.
The lamp A is off.

attribute.title: flat_field_lamp_b_status
attribute.description: This value shall contain a character string that gives a status of flat field (FF) lamp B for n-th sub image, where n is sequence_number. FF lamps are attached in front of ONC-T lens system for calibration.

PermissibleValue.valueMeaning: The lamp B is on, and the voltage mode is high.
The lamp B is on, and the voltage mode is low.
The lamp B is off.

attribute.title: sequence_number
attribute.description: This value shall contain a non-negative integer that gives a sequence number of a series of sub images.

attribute.title: spacecraft_clock_count
attribute.description: This value shall contain a hexadecimal number that gives a spacecraft clock count at the end of image acquisition for n-th sub image, where n is sequence_number.

attribute.title: t_camera_selection_status
attribute.description: This value shall contain a string that gives a selection status of ONC-T camera head by ONC-AE for n-th sub image, where n is sequence_number.

PermissibleValue.valueMeaning: ONC-AE does not select ONC-T camera head for imaging.
ONC-AE selects ONC-T camera head for imaging.

attribute.title: t_driving_status
attribute.description: This value shall contain a string that gives a driving status of ONC-T camera head for n-th sub image, where n is sequence_number.

PermissibleValue.valueMeaning: ONC-T camera head does not drive.
ONC-T camera head drives.

attribute.title: t_exposure_duration

attribute.title: bolometer_temperature
attribute.description: Uncooled micro-bolometer array temperature in the detector package of TIR-S. This is kept at a temperature of peltier_desired_temperature (nominally 40 degrees Celsius) +/- 0.5 degrees Celsius during observation period. This temperature is sampled in the timing of acquiring image.

attribute.title: calibration_lookup_table_file_name
attribute.description: Lookup table file name for conversion between radiant flux and DN of image.

attribute.title: case_temperature
attribute.description: Case temperature of TIR-S. This is kept at a constant temperature during observation period. This temperature is sampled in the timing of acquiring image.

attribute.title: lens_temperature
attribute.description: Lens temperature of TIR-S. The lens of TIR-S is kept at a constant temperature during observation period. This temperature is sampled in the timing of acquiring image.

attribute.title: number_of_bit_shift
attribute.description: This value means number of bit shifts applied to the image onboard. The raw image is 12-bit data without bit shift. The stacked images are 16-, 17-, 18-, and 19-bits before bit shift, and are applied bit shift of 1, 2, 3, and 4, respectively, to acquire data with bitdepth of 15-bit.

PermissibleValue.valueMeaning: No bit shift is applied.
One bit shift is applied for 16 frame stacked image.
Two bit shifts are applied for 32 frame stacked image.
Three bit shifts are applied for 64 frame stacked image.
Four bit shifts are applied for 128 frame stacked image.

attribute.title: package_temperature
attribute.description: Detector package temperature of TIR-S. This is kept at a constant temperature during observation period. This temperature is sampled in the timing of acquiring image.

attribute.title: peltier_desired_temperature

PermissibleValue.valueMeaning: Desired temperature is set to 10 degrees Celsius.
